rdfs:label: Anatomical-landmark
dc:description: A collection of specific points on the human body used for anatomical and sensor placement reference.
omn:EquivalentTo: dc:source "Original", rdfs:comment "Body landmarks are used to standardize sensor placement."

rdfs:label: Head-landmark
dc:description: Points on the head used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Inion
dc:description: The most prominent point of the occipital bone at the back of the head.

rdfs:label: Left-helix-tragus-junction-LHJ
dc:description: The point where the helix meets the tragus of the left ear.

rdfs:label: Mastoid-process
dc:description: The process of the temporal bone behind the ear.

rdfs:label: Nasion
dc:description: The midpoint between the eyes just above the bridge of the nose.

rdfs:label: Right-helix-tragus-junction-RHJ
dc:description: The point where the helix meets the tragus of the right ear.

rdfs:label: Vertex
dc:description: The highest point on the head in the midline.

rdfs:label: Midpoint-between-mastoid-processes-MMP
dc:description: The midpoint between the mastoid processes.

rdfs:label: Torso-chest-landmark
dc:description: Points on the chest used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Acromion-process
dc:description: The outermost point of the shoulder blade.

rdfs:label: Vertebra-prominens-C7
dc:description: The seventh cervical vertebra at the base of the neck.

rdfs:label: Xiphoid-process
dc:description: The small cartilaginous process at the lower end of the sternum.

rdfs:label: Suprasternal-Notch-Jugular-Notch
dc:description: The notch at the top of the sternum.

rdfs:label: Abdomen-landmark
dc:description: Points on the abdomen used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Umbilicus
dc:description: The navel or belly button.

rdfs:label: Anterior-Superior-Iliac-Spine-ASIS
dc:description: The forwardmost point of the iliac crest.

rdfs:label: Posterior-Superior-Iliac-Spine-PSIS
dc:description: The rearmost point of the iliac crest.

rdfs:label: Hand-landmark
dc:description: Points on the hand used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Radial-Styloid-Process-RSP
dc:description: The bony prominence on the radius bone at the wrist.

rdfs:label: Ulnar-Styloid-Process-USP
dc:description: The bony prominence on the ulna bone at the wrist.

rdfs:label: Third-Metacarpophalangeal-Joint-MCP
dc:description: The knuckle of the middle finger.

rdfs:label: Upper-arm-landmark
dc:description: Points on the upper arm used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Acromion
dc:description: The outermost point of the shoulder blade.

rdfs:label: Medial-Humerus-Epicondyle-MHE
dc:description: The medial epicondyle of the humerus.

rdfs:label: Lateral-Humerus-Epicondyle-LHE
dc:description: The lateral epicondyle of the humerus.

rdfs:label: Forearm-landmark
dc:description: Points on the forearm used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Radial-Styloid-Process-RSP
dc:description: The bony prominence on the radius bone at the wrist.

rdfs:label: Ulnar-Styloid-Process-USP
dc:description: The bony prominence on the ulna bone at the wrist.

rdfs:label: Lateral-Humerus-Epicondyle-LHE
dc:description: The lateral epicondyle of the humerus.

rdfs:label: Thigh-landmark
dc:description: Points on the thigh used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Greater-Trochanter
dc:description: The large prominence at the proximal end of the femur.

rdfs:label: Femur-Medial-Epicondyle-FME
dc:description: The medial epicondyle of the femur.

rdfs:label: Femur-Lateral-Epicondyle-FLE
dc:description: The lateral epicondyle of the femur.

rdfs:label: Lower-leg-landmark
dc:description: Points on the lower leg used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Lateral-Malleolus-LM
dc:description: The bony prominence on the lateral side of the ankle.

rdfs:label: Medial-Malleolus-MM
dc:description: The bony prominence on the medial side of the ankle.

rdfs:label: Tibial-Tuberosity
dc:description: The bony prominence on the tibia at the knee.

rdfs:label: Foot-landmark
dc:description: Points on the foot used as reference landmarks.

rdfs:label: Calcaneal-Tuberosity-CT
dc:description: The bony prominence at the heel.

rdfs:label: First-Metatarsal-Head-FME
dc:description: The tip of the big toe.

rdfs:label: Lateral-Malleolus-LM
dc:description: The bony prominence on the lateral side of the ankle.

rdfs:label: Medial-Malleolus-MM
dc:description: The bony prominence on the medial side of the ankle.
